  "prompt": "How many people graduate in India every year (with at least a bachelors degree)?",
  "response": "The number of people graduating in India with at least a bachelor's degree each year can vary significantly based on the data source and methodology used for counting. However, according to various reports and studies, it is estimated that millions of students graduate from higher education institutions annually. As of recent estimates over the last few years, this number is generally cited to be above 8 million graduates per year.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information, you should refer to data published by the Ministry of Education, the All India Survey on Higher Education (AISHE), or similar authoritative sources.",
